            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "ἘΜΠΑΊΖΕΙΝ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Mockers",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", that is, men to whom the holy (not merely the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "resurrection",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", Grotius) serves for mockery. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ΛΑΛΕῖΝ ὙΠΈΡΟΓΚΑ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "ΛΑΛΕῖΝ ὙΠΈΡΟΓΚΑ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is a ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἘΜΠΑΊΖΕΙΝ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "ἘΜΠΑΊΖΕΙΝ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of the holy (which Hofmann without reason denies); this is naturally united with a surrender to their own lusts; therefore ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ΚΑΤᾺ ΤᾺς ἙΑΥΤῶΝ ἘΠΙΘΥΜΊΑς ΠΟΡΕΥΌΜΕΝΟΙ ΤῶΝ ἈΣΕΒΕΙῶΝ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "ΚΑΤᾺ ΤᾺς ἙΑΥΤῶΝ ἘΠΙΘΥΜΊΑς ΠΟΡΕΥΌΜΕΝΟΙ ΤῶΝ ἈΣΕΒΕΙῶΝ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ΤῶΝ ἈΣΕΒΕΙῶΝ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "ΤῶΝ ἈΣΕΒΕΙῶΝ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", an echo of the saying of Enoch, is placed emphatically at the close, in order to render prominent the character and aim of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἘΠΙΘΥΜΊΑΙ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "ἘΠΙΘΥΜΊΑΙ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "That the apostles in their writings frequently prophesied of the entrance of heretical and ungodly men into the church, is well known; comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 20:29",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Timothy 4:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Timothy 3:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ff.; yet ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἘΜΠΑΊΖΕΙΝ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "ἘΜΠΑΊΖΕΙΝ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is not elsewhere stated as a characteristic mark of these men; this is only the case in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Peter 3:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where, however, the mockery is referred only to the denial of the advent of Christ.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "[42] Why Jude should not have intended to comfort his readers by reminding them of what the apostles had, at an earlier period, said of the appearance of these men, as he here describes them, cannot be perceived (against Hofmann).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "[43] Entirely without reason, Schott maintains that the intervening words: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ὅτι ἔλεγον ὑμῖν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", prove that Jude will here give a verbal quotation, and that this must be a ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "writing",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " earlier directed to the readers. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ὅτι ἐλ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ὑμ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". simply introduces the statement of the contents of the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ῥήματα",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", which were earlier spoken by ths apostles. The plural is not to be referred to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "one",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " apostle, and the verb does not in the least degree indicate that this word was ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "written",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Expositor's Greek Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jude 1:17-19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The Faithful are bidden to call to mind the warnings of the Apostles",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The Apostles warned you repeatedly that in the last time there would arise mockers led away by their own carnal lusts. It is these that are now breaking up the unity of the Church by their invidious distinctions, men of unsanctified minds, who have not the Spirit of God. See Introduction on the Early Heresies in the larger edition.",
        "children": []
      },
